<subSubSection pageId="147" pageNumber="908" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="147.[1460,2669,2540,3481]" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1460,1695,3211,3244]" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The holotype was captured roosting in an abandoned gold mine. All individuals found roosting were in cracks and crevices in rocks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="147" pageNumber="908" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="147.[1460,2669,2540,3481]" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1462,2154,3290,3323]" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
All roosting bats known to date were solitary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
